[[Категория:Информация]]
<poem>

«Технический» текст переводить не надо. Только то, что в кавычках.

----


label start:
    
    stop music
    
    scene one
    with dissolve
    
    $ renpy.pause(2.0)
    
    scene bg black
    with dissolve
    
    $ renpy.pause(1.0)
    
    "July 16th, 1905."
    
    play music "funeral.mp3"
    
    "The rain pours outside."
    
    play sound "rain01.mp3"

    scene bg cemetery
    with fade

    "It was raining a week ago as well."
    
    "When it happened."
    
    scene bg cemetery
    with flash
    
    "They said she drowned."
    
    "Her horse and buggy went off the New York and Brooklyn Bridge."
    
    priest "Here we honor..."
    
    "They never found the body. Only the buggy itself surfaced after much searching."
    
    priest "Her time had not come yet. So young, so vibrant, so full of youth..."
    
    "We were engaged to be married only a week later."
    
    "The circumstances surrounding her death were sketchy. Apparently, her buggy had been one of only two buggies on the bridge at the time."
    
    "9:03 AM. The time stuck with me. I was at home, sleeping, when they came to tell me."
    
    "The priest has stopped his incessant droning."
    
    "The crowds start moving away."
    
    "I guess it's time for me to leave, too."
    
    scene bg street2
    with fade
    
    "It's still raining."
    
    play sound "rain01.mp3"
    
    "What miserable weather..."
    
    "I'm miserable..."
    
    j "Woe is me!!!!"
    
    "The people in the street stop to stare..."
    
    "I guess I'll slip into this alleyway to escape the stares of bystanders..."
    
    scene bg alleyway2
    with fade
    
    "This alleyway seems to be empty."
    
    "Empty like my heart."
    
    j "Why did Gladys have to die?!"
    
    j "She touched my heart... She made me whole... She..."
    
    "Oh, look, a bar!"
    
    j "Hooray, BEER!"
    
    play sound "door03.wav"
    
    "..."
    
    scene bg bar
    with fade
    stop music
    play music "members only.mp3"
    
    "The air is warm and hazy."
    
    j "Give me a martini, shaken, not stirred."
    
    "What am I saying..."
    
    "I sit down at one of the stools."
    
    "A girl is sitting next to me."
    
    show m embarrassed
    with dissolve
    
    m1 "..."
    
    "She looks... depressed..."
    
    j "Hey, miss, would like to come over my place later?"
    
    "She glares."
    
    show m angry
    with dissolve
    
    "I guess she's not depressed."
    
    show m yelling
    with dissolve
    
    m1 "Who do you think you are?"
    
    show m angry
    with dissolve
    
    bartender "Umm, sir, here's your drink... shaken not stirred...?"
    
    play sound "glass.wav"
    
    "The bartender runs away from the approaching storm..."
    
    "Maybe I should slip away too..."
    
    "Just as I get up to run..."
    
    show m yelling
    with dissolve
    
    m1 "Don't you dare run away!"
    
    "Crap."
    
    m1 "That's right. I'm talking to you."
    
    "Double crap..."
    
    m1 "You know, I HATE people like you. You think that you can pick up any girl you want. Well, today, MISTER, you have another thing coming."
    
    show m angry
    with dissolve
    
    "....why me....?"
    
    "Wait a minute. Why am I letting a girl talk me down? I'll show HER who I am..."
    
    j "Wait, let me explain!"
    
    "Here's where I go in for the kill..."
    
    j "My fiancé just died, and I'm just drowning away my sorrows in martinis and women... PLEASE DON'T KILL ME!"
    
    "Oops."
    
    show m yelling
    with dissolve
    
    m1 "Oh, spare the explanation, I'm too dizzy to hurt you right now..."
    
    show m thinking
    with dissolve
    
    "She slumps back into her seat."
    
    "I guess I'm off the hook for now."
    
    "She suddenly sits up in her seat."
    
    show m yelling
    with dissolve
    
    m1 "You say your fiancé just died?"
    
    show m angry
    with dissolve
    
    "Oh boy, another teary-eyed sympathetic girl..."
    
    j "Yeah, her horse and buggy kind of... rolled off the bridge..."
    
    show m shocked
    with dissolve
    
    m1 "Oh..."
    
    show m embarrassed
    with dissolve
    
    "Mmmmm, awkward silence. My favorite."
    
    show m yelling
    with dissolve
    
    m1 "Well, I'm sorry, ok?"
    
    show m embarrassed
    with dissolve
    
    j "..."
    
    m1 "..."
    
    j "..."
    
    m1 "..."
    
    j "..."
    
    "...this is fun..."
    
    show m yelling
    with dissolve
    
    m1 "Well, in case you were wondering, my name's Melissa Tempse, but you can call me Mel."
    
    show m angry
    with dissolve
    
    "I don't care..."
    
    j "My name's Joshua McDermouth, but you call me what I tell you to call me. And I say, call me Joshua."
    
    "Ah, aren't I smooth with women? This is why people call me..."
    
    play sound "punch.wav"
    show bg bar
    with hpunch
    
    j "OWWW! WHAT THE HELL WAS THAT FOR?"
    
    show m smug
    with dissolve
    
    m "That was for you being a jerk."
    
    "What the..."
    
    play sound "punch.wav"
    show bg bar
    with vpunch
    show m smug
    
    m "And that was just because I don't like you."
    
    "Ah... I think my vision's going out..."
    
    show bg black
    with fade
    
    "Oh, you bitch..."
    
    hide m smug
    with dissolve
    stop music
</poem>
